1 (1) to examine the trends and patterns of domestic violence-related
2 fatalities and near-fatal instances of domestic violence in Vermont;
3 (2) to identify barriers to safety, the strengths and weaknesses in
4 communities, and systemic responses to domestic violence;
5 (3) to educate the public, service providers, and policymakers about
6 domestic violence fatalities and near-fatal instances of domestic violence and
7 strategies for intervention and prevention; and
8 (4) to recommend policies, practices, and services that will encourage
9 collaboration and reduce fatalities and near-fatal instances of domestic
10 violence due to domestic violence.
(b) The Commission is intended to reflect communities throughout
Vermont and appointing authorities shall strive to appoint persons from
different racial and ethnic backgrounds, persons with a disability, and persons
who identify as LGBTQ+. The Commission shall comprise 17 22 23
members, consisting of the following:
