4 (d) The proceedings and records of the Commission are confidential and
5 are not subject to subpoena, discovery, or introduction into evidence in a civil
6 or criminal action. The Commission shall disclose conclusions and
7 recommendations upon request, but may not disclose information, records, or
8 data that are otherwise confidential, such as autopsy records. The Commission
9 shall not use the information, records, or data for purposes other than those
10 designated by subsections (a) and (g) of this section.
11 (e) The Commission is authorized to require any person appearing before it
12 to sign a confidentiality agreement created by the Commission in order to
13 maintain the confidentiality of the proceedings. In addition, the Commission
14 may enter into agreements with nonprofit organizations and private agencies to
15 obtain otherwise confidential information.
16 (f) Commission meetings are confidential, and shall be exempt from
17 1 V.S.A. chapter 5, subchapter 2 (open meetings law). Commission records
